{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":464,"text":"I'm going to talk about consciousness."},{"time":3081,"text":"Why consciousness?"},{"time":4561,"text":"Well, it's a curiously neglected subject,"},{"time":7387,"text":"both in our scientific\nand our philosophical culture."},{"time":10951,"text":"Now why is that curious?"},{"time":12223,"text":"Well, it is the most important\naspect of our lives"},{"time":15733,"text":"for a very simple, logical reason,"},{"time":17691,"text":"namely, it's a necessary\ncondition on anything"},{"time":20088,"text":"being important in our lives\nthat we're conscious."},{"time":22565,"text":"You care about science, philosophy,\nmusic, art, whatever --"},{"time":25724,"text":"it's no good if you're\na zombie or in a coma, right?"},{"time":29202,"text":"So consciousness is number one."},{"time":31546,"text":"The second reason is that when people do"},{"time":34014,"text":"get interested in it,\nas I think they should,"},{"time":36330,"text":"they tend to say\nthe most appalling things."},{"time":39181,"text":"And then, even when they're\nnot saying appalling things"},{"time":41825,"text":"and they're really trying\nto do serious research,"},{"time":44183,"text":"well, it's been slow.\nProgress has been slow."},{"time":47324,"text":"When I first got interested\nin this, I thought, well,"},{"time":50464,"text":"it's a straightforward problem in biology."},{"time":52670,"text":"Let's get these brain stabbers\nto get busy and figure out"},{"time":55167,"text":"how it works in the brain."},{"time":56051,"text":"So I went over to UCSF and I talked to all"},{"time":58075,"text":"the heavy-duty neurobiologists there,"},{"time":59868,"text":"and they showed some impatience,"},{"time":61444,"text":"as scientists often do when you\nask them embarrassing questions."},{"time":64827,"text":"But the thing that struck me is,\none guy said in exasperation,"},{"time":68585,"text":"a very famous neurobiologist,\nhe said, \"Look,"},{"time":70752,"text":"in my discipline it's okay to be\ninterested in consciousness,"},{"time":74175,"text":"but get tenure first. Get tenure first.\""},{"time":77742,"text":"Now I've been working\non this for a long time."},{"time":80460,"text":"I think now you might actually get tenure"},{"time":82438,"text":"by working on consciousness."},{"time":83796,"text":"If so, that's a real step forward."},{"time":86342,"text":"Okay, now why then is this\ncurious reluctance"},{"time":89247,"text":"and curious hostility to consciousness?"},{"time":91145,"text":"Well, I think it's a combination\nof two features"},{"time":93875,"text":"of our intellectual culture"},{"time":95780,"text":"that like to think they're\nopposing each other"},{"time":98306,"text":"but in fact they share\na common set of assumptions."},{"time":101929,"text":"One feature is the tradition\nof religious dualism:"},{"time":105891,"text":"Consciousness is not a part\nof the physical world."},{"time":109216,"text":"It's a part of the spiritual world."},{"time":111143,"text":"It belongs to the soul,"},{"time":112679,"text":"and the soul is not a part\nof the physical world."},{"time":115975,"text":"That's the tradition of God,\nthe soul and immortality."},{"time":119006,"text":"There's another tradition\nthat thinks it's opposed to this"},{"time":121111,"text":"but accepts the worst assumption."},{"time":123215,"text":"That tradition thinks that we are heavy-duty\nscientific materialists:"},{"time":127293,"text":"Consciousness is not a part\nof the physical world."},{"time":130758,"text":"Either it doesn't exist at all,\nor it's something else,"},{"time":133404,"text":"a computer program\nor some damn fool thing,"},{"time":136054,"text":"but in any case it's not part of science."},{"time":139249,"text":"And I used to get in an argument\nthat really gave me a stomachache."},{"time":141457,"text":"Here's how it went."},{"time":143076,"text":"Science is objective,\nconsciousness is subjective,"},{"time":147108,"text":"therefore there cannot be\na science of consciousness."},{"time":150435,"text":"Okay, so these twin\ntraditions are paralyzing us."},{"time":156939,"text":"It's very hard to get\nout of these twin traditions."},{"time":159807,"text":"And I have only one real\nmessage in this lecture,"},{"time":162825,"text":"and that is, consciousness\nis a biological phenomenon"},{"time":166209,"text":"like photosynthesis, digestion, mitosis --"},{"time":169098,"text":"you know all the biological phenomena\n-- and once you accept that,"},{"time":173433,"text":"most, though not all, of the hard problems"},{"time":176072,"text":"about consciousness simply evaporate."},{"time":178347,"text":"And I'm going to go through some of them."},{"time":180400,"text":"Okay, now I promised you to tell you some"},{"time":182733,"text":"of the outrageous things\nsaid about consciousness."},{"time":185472,"text":"One: Consciousness does not exist."},{"time":189072,"text":"It's an illusion, like sunsets."},{"time":191302,"text":"Science has shown sunsets\nand rainbows are illusions."},{"time":196367,"text":"So consciousness is an illusion."},{"time":198290,"text":"Two: Well, maybe it exists,\nbut it's really something else."},{"time":201545,"text":"It's a computer program\nrunning in the brain."},{"time":205326,"text":"Three: No, the only thing\nthat exists is really behavior."},{"time":209140,"text":"It's embarrassing how influential\nbehaviorism was,"},{"time":212748,"text":"but I'll get back to that."},{"time":214103,"text":"And four: Maybe consciousness exists,"},{"time":216837,"text":"but it can't make\nany difference to the world."},{"time":219052,"text":"How could spirituality move anything?"},{"time":221772,"text":"Now, whenever somebody\ntells me that, I think,"},{"time":223987,"text":"you want to see spirituality\nmove something?"},{"time":226277,"text":"Watch. I decide consciously\nto raise my arm,"},{"time":229129,"text":"and the damn thing goes up. (Laughter)"},{"time":231738,"text":"Furthermore, notice this:"},{"time":235509,"text":"We do not say, \"Well, it's a bit\nlike the weather in Geneva."},{"time":239504,"text":"Some days it goes up and some days\nit doesn't go up.\""},{"time":242152,"text":"No. It goes up whenever\nI damn well want it to."},{"time":244807,"text":"Okay. I'm going to tell\nyou how that's possible."},{"time":247117,"text":"Now, I haven't yet given you a definition."},{"time":250616,"text":"You can't do this if you\ndon't give a definition."},{"time":252974,"text":"People always say consciousness\nis very hard to define."},{"time":255960,"text":"I think it's rather easy to define"},{"time":257843,"text":"if you're not trying to give\na scientific definition."},{"time":260052,"text":"We're not ready\nfor a scientific definition,"},{"time":262332,"text":"but here's a common-sense definition."},{"time":264118,"text":"Consciousness consists\nof all those states of feeling"},{"time":266920,"text":"or sentience or awareness."},{"time":268988,"text":"It begins in the morning when you\nwake up from a dreamless sleep,"},{"time":272546,"text":"and it goes on all day\nuntil you fall asleep"},{"time":275015,"text":"or die or otherwise become unconscious."},{"time":278213,"text":"Dreams are a form of consciousness\non this definition."},{"time":281333,"text":"Now, that's the common-sense definition.\nThat's our target."},{"time":284235,"text":"If you're not talking about that,\nyou're not talking about consciousness."},{"time":287736,"text":"But they think, \"Well, if that's it,\nthat's an awful problem."},{"time":291220,"text":"How can such a thing exist\nas part of the real world?\""},{"time":295178,"text":"And this, if you've ever\nhad a philosophy course,"},{"time":297536,"text":"this is known as the famous\nmind-body problem."},{"time":300287,"text":"I think that has a simple solution too.\nI'm going to give it to you."},{"time":303550,"text":"And here it is: All of our conscious\nstates, without exception,"},{"time":307552,"text":"are caused by lower-level\nneurobiological processes in the brain,"},{"time":313077,"text":"and they are realized in the brain"},{"time":315258,"text":"as higher-level or system features."},{"time":317592,"text":"It's about as mysterious\nas the liquidity of water."},{"time":320748,"text":"Right? The liquidity is not\nan extra juice squirted out"},{"time":324223,"text":"by the H2O molecules."},{"time":325913,"text":"It's a condition that the system is in."},{"time":328791,"text":"And just as the jar full of water\ncan go from liquid to solid"},{"time":333953,"text":"depending on the behavior\nof the molecules,"},{"time":336025,"text":"so your brain can go\nfrom a state of being conscious"},{"time":338902,"text":"to a state of being unconscious,"},{"time":340542,"text":"depending on the behavior\nof the molecules."},{"time":343528,"text":"The famous mind-body\nproblem is that simple."},{"time":347913,"text":"All right? But now we get\ninto some harder questions."},{"time":351090,"text":"Let's specify the exact\nfeatures of consciousness,"},{"time":354534,"text":"so that we can then answer\nthose four objections"},{"time":357006,"text":"that I made to it."},{"time":358293,"text":"Well, the first feature is,\nit's real and irreducible."},{"time":362560,"text":"You can't get rid of it."},{"time":364614,"text":"You see, the distinction\nbetween reality and illusion"},{"time":368785,"text":"is the distinction between how things"},{"time":371454,"text":"consciously seem to us\nand how they really are."},{"time":375328,"text":"It consciously seems like there's --"},{"time":377204,"text":"I like the French \"arc-en-ciel\" â€”"},{"time":378872,"text":"it seems like there's an arch in the sky,"},{"time":381070,"text":"or it seems like the sun\nis setting over the mountains."},{"time":384850,"text":"It consciously seems to us,\nbut that's not really happening."},{"time":387947,"text":"But for that distinction between"},{"time":389874,"text":"how things consciously seem\nand how they really are,"},{"time":392375,"text":"you can't make that distinction\nfor the very existence of consciousness,"},{"time":396430,"text":"because where the very existence\nof consciousness is concerned,"},{"time":400281,"text":"if it consciously seems to you\nthat you are conscious,"},{"time":403261,"text":"you are conscious."},{"time":405146,"text":"I mean, if a bunch of experts\ncome to me and say,"},{"time":408500,"text":"\"We are heavy-duty neurobiologists\nand we've done a study"},{"time":411191,"text":"of you, Searle, and we're\nconvinced you are not conscious,"},{"time":413941,"text":"you are a very cleverly\nconstructed robot,\""},{"time":416013,"text":"I don't think, \"Well, maybe these\nguys are right, you know?\""},{"time":419282,"text":"I don't think that for a moment,\nbecause, I mean,"},{"time":421845,"text":"Descartes may have made a lot\nof mistakes, but he was right about this."},{"time":424755,"text":"You cannot doubt the existence\nof your own consciousness."},{"time":427710,"text":"Okay, that's the first\nfeature of consciousness."},{"time":430020,"text":"It's real and irreducible."},{"time":431824,"text":"You cannot get rid of it\nby showing that it's an illusion"},{"time":435055,"text":"in a way that you can\nwith other standard illusions."},{"time":438284,"text":"Okay, the second feature is this one"},{"time":440816,"text":"that has been such\na source of trouble to us,"},{"time":443281,"text":"and that is, all of our conscious states"},{"time":445463,"text":"have this qualitative character to them."},{"time":448427,"text":"There's something that it\nfeels like to drink beer"},{"time":450832,"text":"which is not what it feels\nlike to do your income tax"},{"time":453777,"text":"or listen to music,\nand this qualitative feel"},{"time":456845,"text":"automatically generates a third feature,"},{"time":459406,"text":"namely, conscious states\nare by definition subjective"},{"time":463200,"text":"in the sense that they only exist\nas experienced"},{"time":466155,"text":"by some human or animal subject,"},{"time":468350,"text":"some self that experiences them."},{"time":470223,"text":"Maybe we'll be able to build\na conscious machine."},{"time":472606,"text":"Since we don't know how our brains do it,"},{"time":474759,"text":"we're not in a position, so far,\nto build a conscious machine."},{"time":478894,"text":"Okay. Another feature of consciousness"},{"time":481669,"text":"is that it comes in unified\nconscious fields."},{"time":485820,"text":"So I don't just have the sight\nof the people in front of me"},{"time":488176,"text":"and the sound of my voice\nand the weight of my shoes"},{"time":490890,"text":"against the floor, but they occur to me"},{"time":493065,"text":"as part of one single\ngreat conscious field"},{"time":496547,"text":"that stretches forward and backward."},{"time":498563,"text":"That is the key to understanding"},{"time":500332,"text":"the enormous power of consciousness."},{"time":502771,"text":"And we have not been able\nto do that in a robot."},{"time":505715,"text":"The disappointment of robotics\nderives from the fact"},{"time":508216,"text":"that we don't know how to make\na conscious robot,"},{"time":510574,"text":"so we don't have a machine\nthat can do this kind of thing."},{"time":513623,"text":"Okay, the next feature of consciousness,"},{"time":516131,"text":"after this marvelous\nunified conscious field,"},{"time":519246,"text":"is that it functions\ncausally in our behavior."},{"time":522039,"text":"I gave you a scientific\ndemonstration by raising my hand,"},{"time":525242,"text":"but how is that possible?"},{"time":526992,"text":"How can it be that this\nthought in my brain"},{"time":530756,"text":"can move material objects?"},{"time":532956,"text":"Well, I'll tell you the answer."},{"time":534457,"text":"I mean, we don't know the detailed answer,"},{"time":536481,"text":"but we know the basic part\nof the answer, and that is,"},{"time":539183,"text":"there is a sequence of neuron firings,"},{"time":541476,"text":"and they terminate where the acetylcholine"},{"time":544563,"text":"is secreted at the axon\nend-plates of the motor neurons."},{"time":547384,"text":"Sorry to use philosophical\nterminology here,"},{"time":549504,"text":"but when it's secreted at the axon\nend-plates of the motor neurons,"},{"time":553475,"text":"a whole lot of wonderful things\nhappen in the ion channels"},{"time":556261,"text":"and the damned arm goes up."},{"time":558167,"text":"Now, think of what I told you."},{"time":560291,"text":"One and the same event,"},{"time":562033,"text":"my conscious decision to raise my arm"},{"time":565068,"text":"has a level of description\nwhere it has all of these"},{"time":567863,"text":"touchy-feely spiritual qualities."},{"time":570009,"text":"It's a thought in my brain,\nbut at the same time,"},{"time":572410,"text":"it's busy secreting acetylcholine"},{"time":574396,"text":"and doing all sorts of other things"},{"time":576087,"text":"as it makes its way from the motor cortex"},{"time":578719,"text":"down through the nerve fibers in the arm."},{"time":581416,"text":"Now, what that tells us\nis that our traditional vocabularies"},{"time":585232,"text":"for discussing these issues\nare totally obsolete."},{"time":588616,"text":"One and the same event has\na level of description"},{"time":591873,"text":"where it's neurobiological,\nand another level of description"},{"time":594839,"text":"where it's mental,\nand that's a single event,"},{"time":597030,"text":"and that's how nature works.\nThat's how it's possible"},{"time":599578,"text":"for consciousness to function causally."},{"time":602171,"text":"Okay, now with that in mind,"},{"time":605030,"text":"with going through these various\nfeatures of consciousness,"},{"time":608097,"text":"let's go back and answer\nsome of those early objections."},{"time":611269,"text":"Well, the first one I said was,\nconsciousness doesn't exist,"},{"time":614878,"text":"it's an illusion. Well,\nI've already answered that."},{"time":616712,"text":"I don't think we need to worry about that."},{"time":618736,"text":"But the second one had\nan incredible influence,"},{"time":622092,"text":"and may still be around, and that is,"},{"time":623936,"text":"\"Well, if consciousness exists,\nit's really something else."},{"time":627127,"text":"It's really a digital computer\nprogram running in your brain"},{"time":630890,"text":"and that's what we need to do\nto create consciousness"},{"time":633438,"text":"is get the right program."},{"time":634891,"text":"Yeah, forget about the hardware.\nAny hardware will do"},{"time":637439,"text":"provided it's rich enough and stable\nenough to carry the program.\""},{"time":640606,"text":"Now, we know that that's wrong."},{"time":643164,"text":"I mean, anybody who's thought\nabout computers at all"},{"time":646173,"text":"can see that that's wrong,\nbecause computation"},{"time":648637,"text":"is defined as symbol manipulation,"},{"time":651052,"text":"usually thought of as zeros\nas ones, but any symbols will do."},{"time":653981,"text":"You get an algorithm that you can program"},{"time":657103,"text":"in a binary code,\nand that's the defining trait"},{"time":660210,"text":"of the computer program."},{"time":662261,"text":"But we know that that's purely\nsyntactical. That's symbolic."},{"time":666144,"text":"We know that actual human consciousness\nhas something more than that."},{"time":670159,"text":"It's got a content\nin addition to the syntax."},{"time":673352,"text":"It's got a semantics."},{"time":674849,"text":"Now that argument, I made\nthat argument 30 --"},{"time":677338,"text":"oh my God, I don't want\nto think about it â€”"},{"time":678629,"text":"more than 30 years ago,"},{"time":679971,"text":"but there's a deeper argument\nimplicit in what I've told you,"},{"time":682900,"text":"and I want to tell you that argument\nbriefly, and that is,"},{"time":685943,"text":"consciousness creates\nan observer-independent reality."},{"time":690093,"text":"It creates a reality of money,\nproperty, government,"},{"time":693581,"text":"marriage, CERN conferences,"},{"time":697553,"text":"cocktail parties and summer vacations,"},{"time":700172,"text":"and all of those are creations\nof consciousness."},{"time":702921,"text":"Their existence is observer-relative."},{"time":705756,"text":"It's only relative to conscious\nagents that a piece of paper"},{"time":709259,"text":"is money or that a bunch\nof buildings is a university."},{"time":712106,"text":"Now, ask yourself about computation."},{"time":715980,"text":"Is that absolute, like force and mass\nand gravitational attraction?"},{"time":719649,"text":"Or is it observer-relative?"},{"time":721781,"text":"Well, some computations are intrinsic."},{"time":725308,"text":"I add two plus two to get four."},{"time":727219,"text":"That's going on no matter\nwhat anybody thinks."},{"time":729790,"text":"But when I haul out my pocket calculator"},{"time":732279,"text":"and do the calculation,\nthe only intrinsic phenomenon"},{"time":736061,"text":"is the electronic circuit\nand its behavior."},{"time":739236,"text":"That's the only absolute phenomenon."},{"time":741000,"text":"All the rest is interpreted by us."},{"time":743428,"text":"Computation only exists\nrelative to consciousness."},{"time":747269,"text":"Either a conscious agent\nis carrying out the computation,"},{"time":750044,"text":"or he's got a piece of machinery that admits\nof a computational interpretation."},{"time":753830,"text":"Now that doesn't mean\ncomputation is arbitrary."},{"time":756755,"text":"I spent a lot of money on this hardware."},{"time":759203,"text":"But we have this persistent confusion"},{"time":761349,"text":"between objectivity and subjectivity\nas features of reality"},{"time":766070,"text":"and objectivity and subjectivity\nas features of claims."},{"time":769998,"text":"And the bottom line of this\npart of my talk is this:"},{"time":773164,"text":"You can have a completely\nobjective science,"},{"time":776815,"text":"a science where you make\nobjectively true claims,"},{"time":779727,"text":"about a domain whose existence\nis subjective,"},{"time":783157,"text":"whose existence is in the human brain"},{"time":786392,"text":"consisting of subjective\nstates of sentience"},{"time":788531,"text":"or feeling or awareness."},{"time":790216,"text":"So the objection that you can't have\nan objective science of consciousness"},{"time":794553,"text":"because it's subjective and science\nis objective, that's a pun."},{"time":798761,"text":"That's a bad pun on objectivity\nand subjectivity."},{"time":801470,"text":"You can make objective claims"},{"time":803794,"text":"about a domain that is subjective\nin its mode of existence,"},{"time":807836,"text":"and indeed that's what neurologists do."},{"time":809409,"text":"I mean, you have patients\nthat actually suffer pains,"},{"time":811957,"text":"and you try to get\nan objective science of that."},{"time":814588,"text":"Okay, I promised to refute all these guys,"},{"time":816660,"text":"and I don't have an awful\nlot of time left,"},{"time":818235,"text":"but let me refute a couple more of them."},{"time":820164,"text":"I said that behaviorism ought to be"},{"time":822378,"text":"one of the great embarrassments\nof our intellectual culture,"},{"time":825667,"text":"because it's refuted\nthe moment you think about it."},{"time":828560,"text":"Your mental states are identical\nwith your behavior?"},{"time":831417,"text":"Well, think about the distinction\nbetween feeling a pain"},{"time":834568,"text":"and engaging in pain behavior."},{"time":836271,"text":"I won't demonstrate pain\nbehavior, but I can tell you"},{"time":838259,"text":"I'm not having any pains right now."},{"time":840098,"text":"So it's an obvious mistake. Why\ndid they make the mistake?"},{"time":844218,"text":"The mistake was â€” and you\ncan go back and read"},{"time":846433,"text":"the literature on this, you\ncan see this over and over â€”"},{"time":849124,"text":"they think if you accept\nthe irreducible existence"},{"time":852707,"text":"of consciousness, you're\ngiving up on science."},{"time":855502,"text":"You're giving up on 300\nyears of human progress"},{"time":858573,"text":"and human hope and all the rest of it."},{"time":860407,"text":"And the message I want\nto leave you with is,"},{"time":863222,"text":"consciousness has to become accepted"},{"time":865665,"text":"as a genuine biological phenomenon,"},{"time":868153,"text":"as much subject to scientific analysis"},{"time":870620,"text":"as any other phenomenon in biology,"},{"time":872580,"text":"or, for that matter, the rest of science."},{"time":874734,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":876116,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}